“GIVE YOUR YOUNGER SELF ONE PIECE OF ADVICE”⁣ - @metalsaints 
⁣
to my younger self:⁣
⁣
everyone is on their own journey, just like you are, and every journey is unique ⁣
⁣
don’t undervalue yourself and don’t let anyone else make you feel ‘less than’ for not fitting into societal norms ⁣
⁣
your opinion of you is more important than other peoples’ opinions of you ⁣
⁣
it will free you up when you finally understand that you are not for everyone and everyone is not for you and that is okay, ⁣
the people who are meant to be in your life will love you for you ⁣
⁣
most importantly, love yourself and own your journey 🫶🏼🌅💫 ⁣
⁣
⁣

“TELL US ABOUT ONE OF YOUR PASSIONS” @metalsaints 
⁣
one of my biggest passions: helping others become the best version of themselves ⁣
⁣
I love watching my clients and people in general fall in love with becoming the best version of themselves,⁣
⁣
I love helping them implement new habits - even if it’s something simple like making their beds, gratitude lists, and journaling first thing in the morning⁣
⁣
I love helping them create new structured routines - exercising, mindful nutrition, and listening to what their body is telling them⁣
⁣
and I love witnessing that lightbulb moment when someone’s decided “good enough” or “mediocre” just isn’t for them anymore - they’ve fallen in love with the process, the daily wins, and being consistent over being perfect⁣
⁣
when I started coaching, I realized how much joy comes from being apart of someone’s journey towards betterment, physically or mentally, and it sets my heart on fire ⁣
⁣

@metalsaints “TALK ABOUT AN OBSTACLE THAT YOU CURRENTLY FACE OR HAVE FACED IN THE PAST, HOW DID IT/HOW DOES IT CHALLENGE YOU TO BE BETTER” ⁣ 

I put other peoples’ feelings above my own,⁣
I never want to disappoint anyone,⁣
I’ve wanted to make other people happy instead of making myself happy,⁣
I’ve struggled and do still struggle with setting boundaries and people pleasing ⁣
⁣
as I was growing up and well into my current adult life, it was important to me that I was considered nice/kind/sweet by everyone even if it meant agreeing to do certain things or get into situations I never wanted to be in to begin with ⁣
⁣
as I discovered, it’s mentally exhausting and it never benefited myself or any relationship, it created resentment, anxiousness and feeling emotionally depleted ⁣
⁣
unlearning people-pleasing is a process, ⁣
there are days when I feel confident to speak up and there are days when I feel guilty for doing so, ⁣
but I challenge myself to actually listen to myself and think about what I really want and by doing that I grow into a more authentic version of myself ⁣
⁣
some boundaries may improve relationships and some boundaries may end relationships and that’s okay ⁣
by honoring your truth, your needs and setting boundaries for yourself not only benefits you, but others in your life because you’re able to create more authentic connections and relationships 🩵⁣🌞
⁣
⁣
⁣

as I’ve transitioned from following a meal plan and started approaching eating more intuitively, I’ve really been enjoying cooking, experimenting with new recipes, and taking simple, nourishing dishes and finding ways to elevate + present them,⁣
⁣
when I would diet or follow a structured meal plan, I quickly learned how spices and sauces can make the most simple and basic meals taste amazing and coming up with different recipies was always fun for me 🍝🥙🥣⁣
⁣
@metalsaints asked if we could sit down for dinner with someone, who would it be and why - ⁣
it would be with @gordongram 👨🏼‍🍳 (and ideally he would be the one cooking 🤪)
⁣
he may well be the best in the kitchen and reading his books and watching his shows (something my family and I like to do together weekly) has inspired me to step out of my comfort zone and continue to experiment and create more in the kitchen in a way that supports my health and lifestyle ⁣
⁣
